INSERT INTO `messages` (`id_mes`, `module_mes`, `language_mes`, `message_mes`) VALUES(114, 'polymod', 'en', '<div class="rowComment">&#9;\r\n<h1>Working tags:</h1>\r\n&#9;\r\n<div class="retrait">&#9;&#9;\r\n<h3>Display the content of the tag if the condition is met:</h3>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<div class="retrait">&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code"> &lt;atm-if what=&quot;<span class="keyword">condition</span>&quot;&gt; ... &lt;/atm-if&gt; </span> &#9;&#9;&#9;\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">condition</span> : Condition to meet to display the content of the tag. Common use is to validate the presence of a non negative value. This condition may also take all the valid forms of a PHP condition (see: <a class="admin" href="http://www.php.net/if" target="_blank">The structures of a PHP&nbsp;control</a>). The condition will be met if the value exists or if it is not negative or if it is not equal to false.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&#9;&#9;</div>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<h3>Loop a series of objects:</h3>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<div class="retrait">&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code">&lt;atm-loop on=&quot;<span class="keyword">objets</span>&quot;&gt; ... &lt;/atm-loop&gt;</span> &#9;&#9;&#9;\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">objets</span> : Collection of objects. Employed to treat all objects of a series of multiple objects (multi-object).</li>\r\n    <li>An attribute <span class="keyword">reverse</span> (optional) can be added to inverse the order of the results (valeu: boolean <span class="vertclair">true</span>, <span class="vertclair">false</span>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;The following values will be replaced in the tag: &#9;&#9;&#9;\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="vertclair">{firstloop}</span> : True if the current object is the first of a list of objects.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="vertclair">{lastloop}</span> : True if the current object is the last of a list of objects.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="vertclair">{loopcount}</span> : ID&nbsp;number of the current object in the list of objects.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="vertclair">{lastloop}</span> : True if the current object is the last of a list of objects.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="vertclair">{maxloops}</span> : Number of objects to loop.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&#9;&#9;</div>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<h3>Add an attribute to the XHTML father tag (containing this tag):</h3>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<div class="retrait">&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code"> &lt;atm-parameter attribute=&quot;<span class="keyword">attributeName</span>&quot; value=&quot;<span class="keyword">attributeValue</span>&quot; /&gt; </span> &#9;&#9;&#9;\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">attributeName</span> : Name of the attribute to add.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">attributeValue</span> : Value of the attribute to add.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&#9;&#9;</div>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<h3>Assign a value to a variable:</h3>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<div class="retrait">&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code">&lt;atm-setvar vartype=&quot;<span class="keyword">type</span>&quot; varname=&quot;<span class="keyword">name</span>&quot; value=&quot;<span class="keyword">varValue</span>&quot; /&gt; </span> &#9;&#9;&#9;\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">type </span>: Type of the variable to assign: <span class="vertclair">request</span>, <span class="vertclair">session</span> or <span class="vertclair">var</span>.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">name </span>: Name of the variable to assign. Attention, reassigning an existing variable will delete the former value.</li>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">varValue</span> : Value to assign to the variable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&#9;&#9;</div>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<h3>Reload a zone in AJAX:</h3>\r\n&#9;&#9;\r\n<div class="retrait">&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code">&lt;atm-xml what=&quot;<span class="keyword">condition</span>&quot;&gt; ... &lt;/atm-xml&gt; </span><br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;Allows to reload a specific zone in the page via an AJAX request.<br />\r\nIf the HTTP request calling the current page contains the parameters verifying the attribute <span class="keyword">condition</span>, then only the content of the tag atm-xml will be sent back in response to the HTTP request. The rest of the content of the current page will be ignored.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor further information, consult the <a target="_blank" href="http://doc.automne.ws">Automne manual on line</a> or study the Polymod modules within the Automne demo that use this function. &#9;&#9;&#9;\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="keyword">condition</span> : Condition to meet to obtain the content of the tag atm-xml.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;<strong>Example with the help of JQuery :</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;Your row has the following code:<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code">&lt;atm-xml what=&quot;<span class="keyword">{request:string:out} == ''xml''</span>&quot;&gt;<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ... search news ...<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&lt;/atm-xml&gt;</span><br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;If you use the following AJAX request toward the page containing this row:<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code"> &#9;&#9;&#9;$.ajax({<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;type:&nbsp;&quot;POST&quot;,<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;url:&nbsp;pageURL,<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;data:&nbsp;''<span class="keyword">out=xml</span>&amp;cat='' + $(''#cat'').val(),<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;success:&nbsp;displaySearch<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;}); &#9;&#9;&#9;</span><br />\r\nThen the news search will be reloaded with the parameter of the selected category and only the content of this zone will be returned:<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;<span class="code"> &#9;&#9;&#9;&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;utf-8&quot;?&gt;<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&lt;response xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot; xmlns:xsd=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema&quot;&gt;<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;error&gt;0&lt;/error&gt;<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;data&gt;&lt;![CDATA[<span class="keyword"> ... the content of the atm-xml tag corresponding to the new search launched ... </span>]]&gt;&lt;/data&gt;<br />\r\n&#9;&#9;&#9;&lt;/response&gt; &#9;&#9;&#9;</span> &#9;&#9;</div>\r\n&#9;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
